'''Aalborg Boldspilklub A/S''' (also '''AaB A/S''') is a [[Denmark|Danish]] sports corporation based in [[Aalborg]] [[Denmark]]. Founded July 1, 1987, AaB A/S is most noted for ownership of the professional [[football (soccer)]] team [[AaB Fodbold]]. Other holdings has until included professional handball and hockey teams, a retail sports chain, a conference and sports center and a sports college but all of these activities has been closed or sold off due to financial problems.<ref>*{{cite news|url=http://www.business.dk/sport-underholdning/raedselsregnskab-tvinger-aab-til-nysalg-af-aktier |title=Rædselsregnskab tvinger AaB til nysalg af aktier |trans-title=Horrible Accounting Forces Aab to sell New Shares |first=David |last=Bentow |newspaper=[[Berlingske Tidende]] |language=Danish |date=29 March 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723000055/http://www.business.dk/sport-underholdning/raedselsregnskab-tvinger-aab-til-nysalg-af-aktier |archivedate=23 July 2011 }}</ref> The company's stock is traded on the [[Copenhagen Stock Exchange]] as AaB.

==Management==
AaB A/S is headed by director Lynge Jacobsen and seven board members with Finn V. Nielsen as chairman of the board.
Each department has its own division director.

==Share holders==
At December 31, 2008 Aalborg Boldspilklub A/S had about 9,600 shareholders.
Two companies owned more than 5%. They are [[Nordjyske Holding A/S]] <ref>Which is the company behind [[Nordjyske Medier]] (a local media group)</ref> with 19.8% and [[Sebc Holding ApS]] with 5.3%.<ref>[http://www.aabsport.dk/BC1A9CED-ACE4-497C-B2DF-BB410C0D3658 Aalborg Boldspilklub A/S, Årsrapport 2008 (Annual report 2008)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917105412/http://www.aabsport.dk/BC1A9CED-ACE4-497C-B2DF-BB410C0D3658 |date=September 17, 2010 }}</ref>

