'''Black Velvet''' was a [[revue]] at the [[Hippodrome, London|London Hippodrome]] in 1938 which included Roma Beaumont, and [[Pat Kirkwood (actress)|Pat Kirkwood]] singing the celebrated song "[[My Heart Belongs to Daddy]]", and vocalist/impressionist [[Afrique (singer)|Afrique]].<ref>{{citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jj-0AAAAIAAJ|pages=155|title=Empires, Hippodromes & Palaces|author=Jack Read|year=1985|isbn=978-0-946619-17-7}}</ref>  The show made Pat Kirkwood into Britain's first wartime star and established her career.

