{{About|the film|the soundtrack album of the film|Comment c'est loin (soundtrack)}} {{Infobox film | name = Comment c'est loin | image = Comment c'est loin poster.jpg | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = {{plainlist| * [[Orelsan]] * Christophe Offenstein }} | producer = {{plainlist| * Maxime Delauney * Romain Rousseau }} | screenplay = {{plainlist| * [[Orelsan|Aurélien Cotentin]] * Christophe Offenstein * Stéphanie Murat }} | story = Aurélien Cotentin | based on = {{Based on|''[[Orelsan et Gringe sont les Casseurs Flowters]]''|[[Casseurs Flowters]]}} | starring = {{plainlist| * Orelsan * [[Gringe]] * Seydou Doucouré * Claude Urbiztondo-Llarch * [[Ablaye]] * [[Skread]] <!-- Per billing block --> }} | music = {{plainlist| * Skread * Alexis Rault * Orelsan }} | cinematography = | editing = Jeanne Kef | studio = {{Plainlist| * NoLiTa Cinema * Orange Studio }} | distributor = La Belle Company | released = {{Film date|2015|10|10|FIF Saint-Jean-de-Luz|2015|11|13|Sarlat Film Festival|2015|12|9|France}} | runtime = 90 minutes<ref name="Allocine">{{cite web|url=http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=236147.html |title=''Comment c'est loin'' - film 2015 |work=[[AlloCiné]] |date=9 December 2015 |language=French |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> | country = France | language = French | budget = $2.1 million<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=15576 |title=COMMENT C'EST LOIN |publisher=JP's Box-Office |language=French |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> | gross = $1 million<ref name="BOM">{{cite web |title=Comment c'est loin |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?id=_fCOMMENTCESTLOIN01 |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> }} '''''Comment c'est loin''''' is a 2015 French quasi-autobiographical [[Comedy (genre)|comedy]] film written by French rapper [[Orelsan]] and directed by Orelsan and Christophe Offenstein. The film stars Orelsan and fellow French rapper [[Gringe]], both of whom form the rap duo [[Casseurs Flowters]], and is based on their debut studio album ''[[Orelsan et Gringe sont les Casseurs Flowters]]'', which was released on 15 November 2013.
The film is set over a 24-hour period in the city of [[Caen]], [[Normandy]], and follows Aurélien, known as Orel (Orelsan, as he was formerly known), and Guillaume, known as Gringe (himself). They seek to finish recording their first song together at the request of their producers [[Skread]] (himself) and [[Ablaye]] (himself), but struggle to do so as they wander around the town with friends looking for quick ways to make money and a good time.
''Comment c'est loin'' was premiered at the Saint-Jean-de-Luz International Film Festival on October 10, 2015, as well as being shown at the Sarlat Film Festival on November 13, 2015, before being released to the French public on December 9, 2015. The film has received mixed-to-positive reviews from critics, and grossed $1,001,196 in the domestic box office within its first three weeks.
==Synopsis== After half a decade of doing next to nothing, Orelsan and Gringe are in their mid-thirties as they struggle to complete their first [[Rapping|rap]] album. Their songs are mostly stories of sex and alcohol, reflecting their everyday lives in the city of [[Caen]]. They have never really finished a song and when they meet with their producers, they are faced with a new challenge. Their old issues, the fear of failure, their alcoholic friends and annoying girlfriends serve to stand in their way as they set out to finish their first song within the next 24 hours.
==Cast== * [[Orelsan]] as Aurélien "Orel" Cotentin (himself) * [[Gringe]] as Guillaume "Gringe" Tranchant (himself) * Seydou Doucouré as Bouteille * Claude Urbiztondo-Llarch as Claude (himself) * [[Ablaye]] as Abdoulaye "Ablaye" Doucouré (himself) * [[Skread]] as Matthieu "Skread" Le Carpentier (himself) * Sophie de Fürst as Pauline * Chloé Astor as Arielle * Redouanne Harjane as the fan * Marc Brunet as Aurélien's father * Jeannine Cotentin as Aurélien's grandmother (herself) * Isabelle Alfred as Arielle's mother * Alain Dion as Arielle's father * France Hofnung as Marie * Clément Cotentin as the local radio DJ * Paul Minthe as the hotel manager * Marine Forster Bourdin as the schools inspector
==Production== ===Filming=== [[File:Orelsan promotion.jpg|thumb|right|[[Orelsan]], who made his directing debut with ''Comment c'est loin'', confirmed the beginning of production on [[Instagram]] on 21 March 2015.]] ''Comment c'est loin'' was filmed on location in the city of [[Caen]], [[Lower Normandy]], where Orelsan went to college and met record producer [[Skread]], one of the film's other composers. Orelsan announced the beginning of production on his [[Instagram]] page on 21 March 2015, posting a picture of a copy of the film's script with the working title ''Orel et Gringe'' (''Orel and Gringe'').<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/0f_h_RxKsv/ |title=Instagram photo by OrelSan • Mar 21, 2015 at 6:31pm UTC |date=21 March 2015 |language=French |publisher=Orelsan / [[Instagram]] |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> He posted another picture on 4 May, this time of himself next to Gringe, presumably during a certain scene in the film, announcing in the caption that filming was complete and confirming the film's title as ''Comment c'est loin''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/2RD32RxKqr/ |title=OrelSan on Instagram: "Tournage terminé! Notre premier film est, comme ta frangine le samedi soir, dans la boîte. Il s'appellera: "Comment c'est loin" Cc @greeeenje" |date=4 May 2015 |language=French |publisher=Orelsan / [[Instagram]] |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>
===Music=== {{See also|Comment c'est loin (soundtrack)}} The [[Film score|musical score]] for the film was composed by Alexis Rault, while the soundtrack featured new songs from Casseurs Flowters and produced by Skread. The soundtrack album, which also acts as Casseurs Flowters' second studio album, was released in France along with the film on December 9, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/comment-cest-loin/id1057314102 |title=Comment c'est loin - iTunes |language=French |publisher=[[iTunes]] |date=9 December 2015 |accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> It peaked at number 24 on the French Albums Chart, at number 61 on the Belgian [[Ultratop]] Albums Chart (Wallonia) and at number 83 on the [[Swiss Hitparade]] Albums Chart.<ref name="Lescharts.com">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Casseurs+Flowters&titel=Comment+c%27est+loin&cat=a |title=Lescharts.com – Casseurs Flowters – Comment c'est loin |publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'Édition Phonographique|Les classements single]]|language=French|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> In April 2017, the album was certified platinum in France.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.booska-p.com/new-les-casseurs-flowters-annoncent-3-surprises-video-n73127.html |title=LES CASSEURS FLOWTERS ANNONCENT 3 SURPRISES ! [VIDEO] |language=French |date=3 April 2017 |publisher=BOOSKA-P |accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rap2tess.fr/rap-francais/rapgame/casseurs-flowters-ont-deux-grandes-annonces-a-faire.html |title=Les Casseurs Flowters ont deux grandes annonces à faire ! |language=French |date=4 April 2017 |website=Rap2Tess.fr |accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>
