{{BLP primary sources|date=June 2010}}

'''John Gallagher''' was a [[cartoonist]]. His younger brother was [[George Gately]], creator of [[Heathcliff (comics)|Heathcliff]], and Gallagher assisted on the strip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://heathcliffcomics.com/artists/|title=Heathcliff® the Cat {{!}} Comics|website=heathcliffcomics.com|access-date=2016-04-21}}</ref>  He died in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.andertoons.com/cartoon-blog/2005/03/gag_cartoonist_john_gallagher_dies.html|title = Gag Cartoonist John Gallagher Passes On - Andertoons Cartoon Blog|website = Andertoons Cartoon Blog|language = en-US|access-date = 2016-04-21}}</ref>

==Career==
He received the [[National Cartoonist Society]] Gag Cartoon Award for 1957 and 1971 for his work.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.reuben.org/awards/|title = National Cartoonists Society|website = www.reuben.org|access-date = 2016-04-21}}</ref>

He has also done artwork for ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Search/Default.aspx?action=advanced&artist=%5B%2522John%2520Gallagher%2522%5D|title = Card Search - Search: artist = %22John%20Gallagher%22 - Gatherer - Magic: The Gathering|website = gatherer.wizards.com|access-date = 2016-04-21}}</ref>

